29#include "bus.h"
30#include "pad.h"
31
32#include <core/option.h>

34/*******************************************************************************
35 * i2c-algo-bit
36 ******************************************************************************/
37static int
38nvkm_i2c_bus_pre_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adap)
39{
40 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = container_of(adap, typeof(*bus), i2c);
41 return nvkm_i2c_bus_acquire(bus);
42}
43
44static void
45nvkm_i2c_bus_post_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adap)
46{
47 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = container_of(adap, typeof(*bus), i2c);
48 return nvkm_i2c_bus_release(bus);
49}
50
51static void
52nvkm_i2c_bus_setscl(void *data, int state)
53{
54 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = data;
55 bus->func->drive_scl(bus, state);
56}
57
58static void
59nvkm_i2c_bus_setsda(void *data, int state)
60{
61 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = data;
62 bus->func->drive_sda(bus, state);
63}
64
65static int
66nvkm_i2c_bus_getscl(void *data)
67{
68 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = data;
69 return bus->func->sense_scl(bus);
70}
71
72static int
73nvkm_i2c_bus_getsda(void *data)
74{
75 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = data;
76 return bus->func->sense_sda(bus);
77}
78
79/*******************************************************************************
80 * !i2c-algo-bit (off-chip i2c bus / hw i2c / internal bit-banging algo)
81 ******************************************************************************/
82static int
83nvkm_i2c_bus_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adap, struct i2c_msg *msgs, int num)
84{
85 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = container_of(adap, typeof(*bus), i2c);
86 int ret;
87
88 ret = nvkm_i2c_bus_acquire(bus);
89 if (ret)
90 return ret;
91
92 ret = bus->func->xfer(bus, msgs, num);
93 nvkm_i2c_bus_release(bus);
94 return ret;
95}
96
97static u32
98nvkm_i2c_bus_func(struct i2c_adapter *adap)
99{
100 return I2C_FUNC_I2C | I2C_FUNC_SMBUS_EMUL;
101}
102
103static const struct i2c_algorithm
104nvkm_i2c_bus_algo = {
105 .master_xfer = nvkm_i2c_bus_xfer,
106 .functionality = nvkm_i2c_bus_func,
107};
108
109/*******************************************************************************
110 * nvkm_i2c_bus base
111 ******************************************************************************/
112void
113nvkm_i2c_bus_init(struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus)
114{
115 BUS_TRACE(bus, "init");
116 if (bus->func->init)
117 bus->func->init(bus);
118}
119
120void
121nvkm_i2c_bus_release(struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus)
122{
123 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad = bus->pad;
124 BUS_TRACE(bus, "release");
125 nvkm_i2c_pad_release(pad);
126 mutex_unlock(&bus->mutex);
127}
128
129int
130nvkm_i2c_bus_acquire(struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus)
131{
132 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad = bus->pad;
133 int ret;
134 BUS_TRACE(bus, "acquire");
135 mutex_lock(&bus->mutex);
136 ret = nvkm_i2c_pad_acquire(pad, NVKM_I2C_PAD_I2C);
137 if (ret)
138 mutex_unlock(&bus->mutex);
139 return ret;
140}
141
142int
143nvkm_i2c_bus_probe(struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus, const char *what,
144 struct nvkm_i2c_bus_probe *info,
145 bool (*match)(struct nvkm_i2c_bus *,
146 struct i2c_board_info *, void *), void *data)
147{
148 int i;
149
150 BUS_DBG(bus, "probing %ss", what);
151 for (i = 0; info[i].dev.addr; i++) {
152 u8 orig_udelay = 0;
153
154 if ((bus->i2c.algo == &i2c_bit_algo) && (info[i].udelay != 0)) {
155 struct i2c_algo_bit_data *algo = bus->i2c.algo_data;
156 BUS_DBG(bus, "%dms delay instead of %dms",
157 info[i].udelay, algo->udelay);
158 orig_udelay = algo->udelay;
159 algo->udelay = info[i].udelay;
160 }
161
162 if (nvkm_probe_i2c(&bus->i2c, info[i].dev.addr) &&
163 (!match || match(bus, &info[i].dev, data))) {
164 BUS_DBG(bus, "detected %s: %s",
165 what, info[i].dev.type);
166 return i;
167 }
168
169 if (orig_udelay) {
170 struct i2c_algo_bit_data *algo = bus->i2c.algo_data;
171 algo->udelay = orig_udelay;
172 }
173 }
174
175 BUS_DBG(bus, "no devices found.");
176 return -ENODEV;
177}
178
179void
180nvkm_i2c_bus_del(struct nvkm_i2c_bus **pbus)
181{
182 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = *pbus;
183 if (bus && !WARN_ON(!bus->func)) {
184 BUS_TRACE(bus, "dtor");
185 list_del(&bus->head);
186 i2c_del_adapter(&bus->i2c);
187#ifdef __NetBSD__
188 linux_mutex_destroy(&bus->mutex);
189#else
190 mutex_destroy(&bus->mutex);
191#endif
192 kfree(bus->i2c.algo_data);
193 kfree(*pbus);
194 *pbus = NULL;
195 }
196}
197
198int
199nvkm_i2c_bus_ctor(const struct nvkm_i2c_bus_func *func,
200 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, int id,
201 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus)
202{
203 struct nvkm_device *device = pad->i2c->subdev.device;
204 struct i2c_algo_bit_data *bit;
205#ifndef CONFIG_NOUVEAU_I2C_INTERNAL_DEFAULT
206 const bool internal = false;
207#else
208 const bool internal = true;
209#endif
210 int ret;
211
212 bus->func = func;
213 bus->pad = pad;
214 bus->id = id;
215#ifdef __NetBSD__
216 linux_mutex_init(&bus->mutex);
217#else
218 mutex_init(&bus->mutex);
219#endif
220 list_add_tail(&bus->head, &pad->i2c->bus);
221 BUS_TRACE(bus, "ctor");
222
223 snprintf(bus->i2c.name, sizeof(bus->i2c.name), "nvkm-%s-bus-%04x",
224 dev_name(device->dev), id);
225 bus->i2c.owner = THIS_MODULE;
226 bus->i2c.dev.parent = device->dev;
227
228 if ( bus->func->drive_scl &&
229 !nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvI2C", internal)) {
230 if (!(bit = kzalloc(sizeof(*bit), GFP_KERNEL)))
231 return -ENOMEM;
232 bit->udelay = 10;
233 bit->timeout = usecs_to_jiffies(2200);
234 bit->data = bus;
235 bit->pre_xfer = nvkm_i2c_bus_pre_xfer;
236 bit->post_xfer = nvkm_i2c_bus_post_xfer;
237 bit->setscl = nvkm_i2c_bus_setscl;
238 bit->setsda = nvkm_i2c_bus_setsda;
239 bit->getscl = nvkm_i2c_bus_getscl;
240 bit->getsda = nvkm_i2c_bus_getsda;
241 bus->i2c.algo_data = bit;
242 ret = i2c_bit_add_bus(&bus->i2c);
243 } else {
244 bus->i2c.algo = &nvkm_i2c_bus_algo;
245 ret = i2c_add_adapter(&bus->i2c);
246 }
247
248 return ret;
249}
250
251int
252nvkm_i2c_bus_new_(const struct nvkm_i2c_bus_func *func,
253 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, int id,
254 struct nvkm_i2c_bus **pbus)
255{
256 if (!(*pbus = kzalloc(sizeof(**pbus), GFP_KERNEL)))
257 return -ENOMEM;
258 return nvkm_i2c_bus_ctor(func, pad, id, *pbus);
259}
